Public Works (Department)
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a state organisation (now defunct) responsible for contructing and maintaining public roads, bridges, buildings, etc.; an important provider of largely unskilled employment in remote rural regions during mid and late 20th century and hence also often a source of pilfered equipment or materials
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
